---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro'; import '../../styles/marketing-pages.css'; const guides=[['AI Coder Guide','Install the workflow, understand findings, and move from detection to governed remediation.','/docs/ai-coder-guide/'],['Integration guides','See how Mault maps identity, intent, policy, and evidence to each supported coding tool.','/docs/integrations/'],['How enforcement works','Follow a governed action from authenticated developer through sealed evidence.','/how-it-works/']];
---
<SiteLayout title="Mault Documentation | Start Governing AI Code" description="Mault documentation for setup, coding-agent integrations, policy enforcement, and evidence workflows." canonical="/docs/"><header class="mp-hero"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">Documentation</p><h1 class="display">Deploy control.<br/><span class="gradient-text">Keep developer velocity.</span></h1><p class="lede">Guides for understanding Mault, connecting supported coding tools, and operating deterministic governance.</p></div></header><section class="section"><div class="shell mp-grid-3">{guides.map(([title,copy,href],i)=><a class="mp-card" href={href}><span>0{i+1}</span><h2>{title}</h2><p>{copy}</p><b style="color:var(--green)">Open guide →</b></a>)}</div></section><section class="section mp-band"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">Core model</p><h2 class="mp-section-title">Every action answers five questions.</h2><div class="mp-grid-3"><article class="mp-card"><span>Who</span><h3>Identity</h3><p>Which authenticated developer and agent initiated the action?</p></article><article class="mp-card"><span>What + where</span><h3>Intent and scope</h3><p>What change was requested and which protected boundary is affected?</p></article><article class="mp-card"><span>Why allowed</span><h3>Policy and evidence</h3><p>Which rule decided the outcome and what proof was preserved?</p></article></div></div></section></SiteLayout>
